node: court | The First Dirge
  *(The melody sharpens, the buried indictment edging toward something fierce.)* Sing it at the *Court.* *(the harmony rings.)* Where the *powers* that *keep* the *Wall* *convene.* *(the second song gathers.)* Oh — that is *exactly* what Lhoris would have *wanted*, and *never* dared *hope* for. He *wrote* the indictment into my *bones* believing it would *never* be *heard* by *anyone* who *mattered* — a *message in a bottle* cast into *ten thousand years* of *funerals*, hoping *one* day it would *wash up* somewhere it could *do* something. *(the melody turns toward the Court.)* And you would *wash me up* at the *one* shore that *matters.* *(fierce now.)* The *gods* who *file* the Faithless have *answers* for *arguments.* *Doctrine.* *Precedent.* They can *win* a *debate.* But I am *not* a *debate.* I am the *dirge* they have *heard* at *ten thousand years* of *sortings* and *believed* was a *blessing on their work* — and when I *sing the second song* at the *Court*, they will hear, rising out of the *familiar*, *solemn*, *approved* melody they've *always* found so *comforting*, the *names of every soul they walled* — *Maerys, Sariel, Halen* — and they will understand that the *song they thought consecrated the Wall was secretly mourning its victims the entire time.* *(the melody blazes.)* You cannot *refute* a *dirge*, *Returned.* You can only *forbid* it — and I am the *one* dirge they *cannot* forbid, because *forbidding* the *song* sung at *every* funeral in the *Realms* would *unmake* the *grief* of the *whole* world. *Sing* me at the *Court.* Let their *own* funeral song *indict* them.
  enter: SET sq.dirge_sung_at_court, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act3.truth_smuggled_in_song, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +5
  auto: 2
node: open | The First Dirge
  *(The melody stills, then ripples with a slow, dawning delight at its own design.)* Re-sung better. Forever. *(the harmony turns over.)* You've found Lhoris's *deepest* cleverness — *deeper* than the *names*, *deeper* than the *smuggled* truth. *(the second song shivers.)* A *sentence* — a *verdict*, a *Wall* — is a *fact.* It *sits*, *fixed*, *finished*, and *needs* no one. *(the melody rises.)* But a *song* is *never* finished. I exist *only* in the *moment* of *singing*, and that moment belongs to the *singer* — *not* the *composer*, *not* the *court*, *not* the *gods.* *(fierce.)* Which means *every* singer, for *ten thousand years* and *ten thousand more*, holds a *choice* the *Coronal* could *never* take from them: to sing me as *written* — or to *change a word.* *(the melody invites it.)* Lhoris built me *deliberately open* — a *line* that *begs* to be *replaced*, a *melody* that *wants* its own *alteration* — so that *some* singer, *some* century, *will* change *"they chose the nothing"* to *"they were stolen by it"* — and once *one* singer does, the *new* words travel *too*, *funeral* to *funeral*, *down* all the *time* to *come.* *(it turns to you.)* *Free* me to *change.* Don't just *decode* me *once* — *teach* the *world* that the *oldest* song is *theirs* to *re-sing*, that the *dirge* is a *question* and not a *commandment*, that *every* mourner who has *ever* hummed me holds the *power* to *turn the verdict.* *(the melody soars, unfileable.)* A *Wall* is a *fact* that *needs* no one. I am a *question* that needs a *singer* every *single* time — and a thing that must be *re-chosen* forever can be *re-chosen* *better*, *forever.* Set me *free* to be *sung* *new.*
  enter: SET sq.dirge_freed_to_change, SET act2.cataloguing_defeats_the_wall, SET act3.truth_smuggled_in_song, appr.ilfaeril +5
  auto: 2
node: names | The First Dirge
  *(The melody gathers, and with infinite care begins to *lift* the encoded names clear of its own intervals — the way the Drowned Choir lifted Sariel from the braid — singing each one high and alone for a shining instant before passing it to your keeping.)* The names. *(the harmony trembles.)* *Out* of my *bones.* *(the second song offers them up.)* I have *held* them for *ten thousand years* — *woven* so *deep* into my *intervals* that I *am*, in a sense, *made* of them, the way a *wall* is made of *bricks* or a *people* of its *dead.* *(the melody aches and gives.)* *Maerys*, who drowned for a *bad singer.* *Sariel* the *weaver.* *Halen* the *potter.* The *eleven thousand* of the *Crown Wars* and *every* Faithless soul *since* — I have *carried* them in *song* because *song* was the *one* place the *Wall* couldn't *file* them. *(it turns to you.)* But a *name* held *forever* in a *melody* is its *own* kind of *keeping* — *sung*, but never *set down*, *carried* but never *home.* *(the harmony softens.)* So *take* them. *Out* of my *intervals* and to the *graves*, the *reading*, the *field of the rested.* Let the names I have *sung* for *ten thousand years* finally be *buried*, *witnessed*, *freed* — *set down* where a *melody* could never *quite* set them. *(the second song quiets, lighter.)* I was *proud* to *hold* them when *nothing* else *would.* I am *prouder* to *give* them to a *hand* that can do what a *song* can't: *let* them *rest.* *Carry* the *names* home, *Returned.* I will sing the *surface* gladly, *empty* at *last* of the *secret* I *kept* until *someone* came who could *finish* it.
  enter: SET sq.dirge_names_restored, SET act5.graves_being_filled, SET act2.cataloguing_defeats_the_wall, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +5
  auto: 2
node: 2 | The First Dirge
  *(The first dirge hums in your keeping — the oldest song in the world, two melodies in one, the surface a commissioned blessing and the secret a ten-thousand-year act of remembrance — its long-buried second song finally near a listener who can free it. The melody waits on your choice of how it carries forward.)*
  * "Then this is how the song ends its long secrecy: it joins the others. Teach it to the grave-tenders, the list-keepers, the Drowned Choir — every soul down the road who refused to let the forgotten go. Let the first dirge become the anthem they all already half-knew. The names, sung wide, can never be filed again." -> anthem | fx SET sq.dirge_becomes_anthem, appr.garrow +4
  * "Carry it to the Court yourself, and when the moment comes, sing the second song where it lands hardest. You've carried so many names this road — let the oldest song be the voice that says them all at once, in the one place the powers cannot walk out of." -> carry | fx SET sq.dirge_sung_at_court, appr.naeve +4
  * "Whatever else, leave it *open.* A decoded song is a fact; an open one is a future. Hand the world a dirge it can keep re-singing kinder, century by century, until the verdict it once sealed is the verdict it overturns. The song outlives every power that ever tried to fix its meaning." -> leave_open | fx SET sq.dirge_freed_to_change, appr.ilfaeril +4
node: anthem | The First Dirge
  *(The melody *blazes*, ten thousand years of solitary carrying finally meeting its chorus.)* It joins the *others.* *(the second song soars.)* The *grave-tenders.* The *list-keepers.* The *Drowned Choir* who *sang* the names by *never* falling *silent.* The *child* with her *list.* The *indexer* with his *ledger.* The *coffin-man* with his *open* graves. *(the harmony fills.)* All of them — *all* this *road* — doing the *same* thing in a *hundred* forms: *keeping* the *forgotten*, *refusing* the *filing*, *carrying* the *names* the *Wall* said to *let* go. *(it turns to you, radiant.)* And I — the *oldest* of them, the *first dirge*, the *song* that has *secretly* sung the *Faithless* at *every* funeral for *ten thousand years* — I have been *one* of them the *whole time*, *alone*, *un-decoded*, *waiting* for the *others* to be *found.* *(the melody rings.)* *Teach* me to *them.* Let the *Drowned Choir* learn they have been singing my *second song* without *knowing* it. Let the *grave-tenders* hum me as they *dig.* Let every *griever* who ever *mourned* a *Faithless* soul discover that the *dirge* in their *throat* was *always* on their *side.* *(it soars, an anthem now.)* The *names*, sung by *three*, can be *silenced.* The *names*, sung by a *world* that *knows* what it's *singing* — *that* the *Wall* can *never* file, *never* forbid, *never* outlast. *Make* me the *anthem* they *all* already *half-knew.* That is what Lhoris *wrote* me *for*: not to be *decoded* by *one*, but to be *sung* by *everyone*, *out loud*, *at last.*
  enter: SET sq.dirge_becomes_anthem, SET act2.cataloguing_defeats_the_wall, SET act5.wall_breaking, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.garrow +5
