node: carry | The First Dirge
  *(The melody steadies into fierce, focused purpose.)* Carry me to the *Court.* *(the second song gathers.)* And let me be the *voice* that says them *all* at *once.* *(the harmony rises.)* You have *carried* so *many* names down this *road* — *Halen's*, *Maerys's*, *Sariel's*, the *forbidden* name the *candle* held, the *forty-one* the *reaper* hid — *one* by *one*, *soul* by *soul.* *(it turns to you.)* But I am the *song* that holds them *all*, *woven* together, *eleven thousand* and more, in a *single* melody. *(fierce.)* So when you stand at the *Court*, and the *powers* of the *dead* defend their *Wall* with *doctrine* and *precedent* — let *me* be your *answer.* Not an *argument.* A *dirge.* The *one* they have *heard* at *every* sorting and *believed* was a *blessing* — *singing*, now, in its *true* voice, *every* name they *ever* walled, *rising* out of the *melody* they *trusted.* *(the melody blazes.)* They will have *no* refutation, *Returned. You cannot out-argue a song that is also a* list of your victims. *Carry* me to the *one* court that *cannot* adjourn, and let the *oldest* dirge in the *world* sing the *Faithless* *home* in the *one* room where it *counts.* *(it soars.)* Lhoris *cast* me into *ten thousand years* hoping I'd *wash up* somewhere I could *matter.* *You* are the *shore.* The *Court* is the *moment.* *Sing.*
  enter: SET sq.dirge_sung_at_court, SET act5.the_great_objection, SET act1.mercy_remembered, appr.naeve +5
